"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0725-1461849-olympics-podcast-life-in-the-village-and-handling-hype\", \"text\": \"  For the first episode of the daily RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast, Mikey Stafford is joined by David Gillick and Jessie Barr to discuss handling the hype, look ahead to the opening ceremony and try and predict how many medals Team Ireland can win.  Both Olympians at 400m, Jessie and David are now working at the Games in different capacities - Jessie as a performance psychologist with the Sport Ireland Institute and David as a reporter with RT\\u00c9 Sport.  They are well-placed to discuss the sociology of the Athletes' Village, the perils of walking too far at the Opening Ceremony and the spectre of doping that is never too far away from the Olympics.  We also learn a little about Ireland's 1924 medallists...  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"